If dd(Auth::id()) (or dd($request->user_id) returns null even when you are logged in, it means the request is not passing through the auth middleware session, or you are checking the wrong value.

Let’s fix it systematically.

1️⃣ First Test Correct Variable

Do NOT use:

dd($request->user_id);

Because user_id is not coming from the form.

Instead use:

dd(auth()->id());

or

dd(Auth::id());

Example:

public function store(Request $request)
{
    dd(auth()->id());
}
Expected result
1

If it shows:

null

then authentication is not active for that route.

2️⃣ Confirm You Are Actually Logged In

Open browser and visit:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/dashboard

If it redirects to login, then you are not logged in.

If it shows dashboard → login works.

